text.section:
Notwithstanding § 5-128(b) of this subtitle, a person may purchase more than one regulated firearm in a 30-day period if:
the person applies for and the Secretary approves a multiple purchase; and
the purchase of the regulated firearms is for a private collection or a collector series;
the purchase of the regulated firearms is a bulk purchase from an estate sale;
the purchase is for other purposes similar to items (i) through (iii) of this item.

section.section:
The application for a multiple purchase shall:
list the regulated firearms to be purchased;
state the purpose of the purchase of more than one regulated firearm in a 30-day period;
be witnessed by a licensee or designated law enforcement agency; and
be signed under the penalty of perjury by the firearm applicant.
